The Herald By Daniel Chigunwe
Karanda Bridge deck which is under-construction was last night swept away by heavy rains that have pounded Mount Darwin for the past two days. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-462801 size-full" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/2.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/2.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/2-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" />
Rushinga Member of Parliament Cde Tendai Nyabani confirmed the incident but referred questions to Mt Darwin East legislator Cde Norman Marikisi who was not readily available for comment. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-462799 size-full" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/d16c5571-3852-4539-b1d3-b074a488edd4-1.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/d16c5571-3852-4539-b1d3-b074a488edd4-1.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/d16c5571-3852-4539-b1d3-b074a488edd4-1-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> <img class="aligncenter wp-image-462823 size-full" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/1.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/1.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/1-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> “It’s confirmed the bridge was swept away last night and I have also shared the information on social media but that is not my constituency. The washed away bridge borders Mt Darwin South and Mt Darwin East constituencies,” said Cde Nyabani.   